Hint:
1. How to bitwise detect if there is only one 1-bit in an integer?

What makes 0010 0000, 0001 0000, or 0000 0100, different from, say, 0000 1100?
0010 0000 - 0000 0001 = 0001 1111
0001 0000 - 0000 0001 = 0000 1111
0000 0100 - 0000 0001 = 0000 0011
while
0000 1100 - 0000 0001 = 0000 1011

2. How to different a four's power from a two's power?

math formula hint:
pow(x,k) - 1 = (x-1)( pow(x,k-1)+pow(x,k-2)+pow(x,k-3)+...+pow(x,1)+1 )